s=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3616332\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 20, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ule1665702637317.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ule1665702637317.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ule1665702637317.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ule1665702637317\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Supported Drag Formats (DragFormat) \n  </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specifies the drag-and-drop formats that can be used when dragging objects in this widget.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ule1665702637317__p_d107339e1_d107340e1_d107341e1\">DragFormat<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">DragFormatList</var></p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ule1665702637317__section_jf4_ptk_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1006748e58\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ule1665702637317__p_d107345e1_d107346e1_d107347e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DragFormatList</var> is a Uniface list (GOLD ; separated) of format names.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ule1665702637317__section_dlb_stk_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1006748e70\">Tree Widget</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ule1665702637317__p_d107351e1_d107352e1_d107353e1\">In a tree widget, the drag-and-drop properties are\n        associated with tree item types. The property name incorporates the index number of the\n        defined tree item types. Thus <code class=\"ph codeph\">DragFormat1</code> defines the drag formats for the\n        first defined tree item type.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ule1665702637317__section_est_stk_zwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1006748e82\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ule1665702637317__ul_yzw_ttk_zwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ule1665702637317__li_d42242e1_d42243e1_d42244e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rgn1665702634165.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rgn1665702634165.html\" title=\"Image to use as the background image on the map widget.\">Image Name</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ule1665702637317__li_d42245e1_d42246e1_d42247e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gge1665702634237.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gge1665702634237.html\" title=\"The utree widget enables users to view and navigate structured data as a hierarchy. Uniface provides a logical widget called Tree, which is mapped to utree.\">utree (Tree)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/swj1719500297780.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Drag-and-Drop Formats</a><p>Drag-and-drop formats are global objects that define drag and drop behavior, including the default action, pop-up menu, and icon that are available when performing drag and drop actions in the tree and picture widgets. They are not used for drag-and-drop widgets.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oqr1705583543910.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Create and Maintain Drag-and-Drop Formats</a><p>Drag-and-drop formats determine the actions and context menus for dragging and dropping objects in Tree and Picture widgets in desktop applications. They are maintained and deployed in a runtime library.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eav1719500059023.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Drag and Drop Behavior</a><p>Drag and drop behavior enables the user to select an object and drag it to another location with the mouse. When the mouse button is released, the selected object is copied, moved, or linked to by a shortcut.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616332\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616332\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Supported Drag Formats (DragFormat) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 20, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Supported Drag Formats (DragFormat) Specifies the drag-and-drop formats that can be used when dragging objects in this widget. DragFormat = DragFormatList Description DragFormatList is a Uniface list (GOLD ; separated) of format names. Tree Widget In a tree widget, the drag-and-drop properties are associated with tree item types. The property name incorporates the index number of the defined tree item types. Thus DragFormat1 defines the drag formats for the first defined tree item type. Applies To Image Name utree (Tree) Related Links Drag-and-Drop Formats Drag-and-drop formats are global objects that define drag and drop behavior, including the default action, pop-up menu, and icon that are available when performing drag and drop actions in the tree and picture widgets. They are not used for drag-and-drop widgets. Create and Maintain Drag-and-Drop Formats Drag-and-drop formats determine the actions and context menus for dragging and dropping objects in Tree and Picture widgets in desktop applications. They are maintained and deployed in a runtime library. Drag and Drop Behavior Drag and drop behavior enables the user to select an object and drag it to another location with the mouse. When the mouse button is released, the selected object is copied, moved, or linked to by a shortcut. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}